{% comment %}
  snippets/header-search.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ROW 3b: Search form — text input, voice mic button, submit button.

  VARIABLES (passed in via `with` from sections/header.liquid):
    placeholder  {string}  — input placeholder text.
                             e.g. "What are you looking for?"
                             Falls back to that string if blank.

  GLOBALS READ DIRECTLY:
    routes.search_url  — Shopify's /search endpoint. Required as form action.
    search.terms       — pre-fills the input on the /search results page so
                         the query stays visible after submitting.

  CALLER (sections/header.liquid):
    {% render 'header-search',
       placeholder: section.settings.search_placeholder
    %}

  CRITICAL SHOPIFY REQUIREMENTS (do not remove):
    - action="{{ routes.search_url }}"  — must point to Shopify search route.
    - method="get"                      — Shopify search only accepts GET.
    - <input type="hidden" name="type" value="product"> — scopes results to
      products only. Change to "article" or "page" or remove for all results.
    - <input name="q">                  — Shopify reads this param for the
                                          search query. Name must be "q".

  STEP 3 NOTES (predictive search):
    - Add aria-controls="search-results-listbox" to the text input and
      aria-expanded on the form once a results panel exists.
    - The mic button (data-voice-search) is cosmetic now. Wire to the
      Web Speech API in header.js when ready — no markup changes needed,
      just a JS event listener on [data-voice-search].
    - For predictive search, add data-search-input to the text input so
      header.js can debounce keystrokes and fetch /search/suggest.json.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}

<form
  action="{{ routes.search_url }}"
  method="get"
  role="search"
  class="header__search"
  data-search-form
>
  {% comment %} Scopes Shopify search results to products only {% endcomment %}
  <input type="hidden" name="type" value="product">

  <input
    type="search"
    name="q"
    class="header__search-input"
    placeholder="{{ placeholder | default: 'What are you looking for?' | escape }}"
    aria-label="Search"
    autocomplete="off"
    spellcheck="false"
    value="{{ search.terms | escape }}"
    data-search-input
  >

  {% comment %} Cosmetic now — data-voice-search is the JS hook for Step 3 {% endcomment %}
  <button
    type="button"
    class="header__search-mic"
    aria-label="Voice search"
    data-voice-search
  >
    🎤
  </button>

  <button
    type="submit"
    class="header__search-submit"
    aria-label="Submit search"
  >
    🔍
  </button>
</form>
